OL,3,CChild in induced coma as drink and
OL,4,Cdrug driver crashes
OL,6,FAt around 9.30pm on 30 August last
OL,7,Fyear, Trotter collided with a Skoda
OL,8,FRoomster, travelling in the opposite
OL,9,Fdirection.
OL,11,FAs a result of the smash, one of the
OL,12,Fchildren in Trotter's vehicle
OL,13,Fsustained a number of serious
OL,14,Finjuries, including a deep laceration
OL,15,Fto his forehead, a broken nose, a
OL,16,Ffracture to his right and left collar
OL,17,Fbones, and a fracture to the left side
OL,18,Fof his pelvis. He was placed in an
OL,19,Finduced coma for four days.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
